Task: Rust Chumsky parser: () is not an iterator when folding repeated (BinOp, Expr)

 <p>I've been working on the 'multiplication / division and general expressions' portion of my parser in Rust complains that <code>()</code> is not an iterator when I try to fold over the repeated operator-expr pairs.</p>
<p>What I've tried:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Removing all whitespace handling (<code>.padded_by(ws())</code>)</p>
</li>
<li><p>Boxing parsers</p>
</li>
<li><p>Explicit type annotations</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Here's the relevant code to reproduce my problem:</p>
<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>use chumsky::prelude::*;

#[derive(Debug)]
pub enum BinOp {
    Mul,
    Div,
}

#[derive(Debug)]
pub enum Expr {
    Int(i32),
    Binary {
        left: Box&lt;Expr&gt;,
        op: BinOp,
        right: Box&lt;Expr&gt;,
    },
}

fn parse_mul_op&lt;'a&gt;() -&gt; impl Parser&lt;'a, &amp;'a str, BinOp&gt; {
    just('*').to(BinOp::Mul)
        .or(just('/').to(BinOp::Div))
}

fn parse_primary&lt;'a&gt;() -&gt; impl Parser&lt;'a, &amp;'a str, Expr&gt; {
    text::int(10).map(|s: &amp;str| Expr::Int(s.parse().unwrap()))
}

fn parse_mul_div&lt;'a&gt;() -&gt; impl Parser&lt;'a, &amp;'a str, Expr&gt; {
    let lhs = parse_primary();
    let op_rhs = parse_mul_op().then(parse_primary());

    lhs
        .then(op_rhs.repeated())
        .map(|(mut expr, tail)| {
            for (op, rhs) in tail { // tail `()` is not an iterator ?
                expr = Expr::Binary {
                    left: Box::new(expr),
                    op,
                    right: Box::new(rhs),
                };
            }
            expr
        })
}

fn main() {
    let parser = parse_mul_div();
    let result = parser.parse(&quot;1*2*3&quot;);
    println!(&quot;{:?}&quot;, result);
}
</code></pre>


