1. Use `format!()` to build the doc string at macro expansion time, converting the type to a string with `quote!(#typ).to_string()` (or equivalently `format!("{}", quote!(#typ))`).
2. Use `#[doc = #safety_doc]` attribute syntax instead of `///`, which allows `quote!` to interpolate the string variable `#safety_doc`.

